You have several options when sorting your library inventory display.
The first option is sorting by book name. Selecting this in the drop down menu, then clicking the "Sort!" button will then sort all your data in alphabetical order by the name of each

data.name: LblSearchingHelp.Text
data.value:
Another option on this application is the search feature. Simply type in the name of a book you wish to look for, and press the "Search!" button and it well locate it for you.
This feature is not case sensitive but it does, however, only search by book title. If there is no match found, then a messagebox will display telling you so. If it does find a match, then a new form will show up with all the specific book's information you requested.

If you wish to edit an entry, then select the book from the drop down menu. Once the book is selected it will instantly show the book's information in the textboxes. From here you may alter the contents of these textboxes and click the "Edit" button. This will then bring you back to the display form and show your newly refreshed display with the changes made to the book you selected.
You may also delete an entry. To do this, all you have to do is select the book you wish to remove from the drop down menu and click the "Delete" button. You will be brought back to the display form and you will notice that the book you removed is no longer there.
If you wish to exit the administration panel without making any changes, then all you have to do is click the "Cancel" button and you will be brought back with no problems.
